/p\u003e\n            \u003cp id=\"status-msg\"\u003eFeed the model to avoid hallucination...\u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n        \u003cdiv class=\"slot-machine\"\u003e\n            \u003cdiv class=\"reel\" id=\"reel1\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"reel-strip\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n            \u003cdiv class=\"reel\" id=\"reel2\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"reel-strip\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n            \u003cdiv class=\"reel\" id=\"reel3\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"reel-strip\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n        \u003cbutton id=\"spin-button\"\u003eSPIN (Cost: 10 Tokens)\u003c/button\u003e\n        \u003cdiv class=\"legend\"\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e🤖 🤖 🤖 = AGI Achieved (+100)\u003c/p\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e⚡ ⚡ ⚡ = Overclocked (+50)\u003c/p\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e📉 📉 📉 = Model Collapse (-50)\u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cscript src=\"script.js\"\u003e\u003c/script\u003e\n\u003c/body\u003e\n\u003c/html\u003e\n```\n\n#### 2. CSS (The Aesthetics)\nThe trick here is the `reel-strip`, which is a long vertical column of emojis. We shift its `transform: translateY` to \"spin\" it.\n\n```css\nbody {\n    background: #1a1a1a;\n    color: #00ff41;\n    font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;\n    display: flex;\n    justify-content: center;\n    align-items: center;\n    height: 100vh;\n    margin: 0;\n}\n\n.machine-container {\n    text-align: center;\n    border: 4px solid #333;\n    padding: 2rem;\n    background: #222;\n    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 255, 65, 0.2);\n}\n\n.slot-machine {\n    display: flex;\n    gap: 10px;\n    justify-content: center;\n    margin: 20px 0;\n    background: #000;\n    padding: 10px;\n    border-radius: 8px;\n}\n\n.reel {\n    width: 80px;\n    height: 80px;\n    border: 2px solid #444;\n    overflow: hidden;\n    background: #fff;\n    position: relative;\n}\n\n.reel-strip {\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n    align-items: center;\n    transition: transform 2s cubic-bezier(0.45, 0.05, 0.55, 0.95);\n}\n\n.symbol {\n    width: 80px;\n    height: 80px;\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    justify-content: center;\n    font-size: 2.5rem;\n}\n\nbutton {\n    background: #00ff41;\n    color: #000;\n    border: none;\n    padding: 15px 30px;\n    font-weight: bold;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    font-size: 1.2rem;\n}\n\nbutton:disabled {\n    background: #555;\n    cursor: not-allowed;\n}\n```\n\n#### 3. JavaScript (The Logic)\nWe manage the symbols and the logic to calculate wins based on where the \"strip\" stops.\n\n```javascript\nconst symbols = ['🤖', '⚡', '📉', '🧠', '💰', '🔥'];\nconst SPIN_COST = 10;\nlet tokens = 100;\n\nconst reelStrips = document.querySelectorAll('.reel-strip');\nconst spinBtn = document.getElementById('spin-button');\nconst tokenDisplay = document.getElementById('token-count');\nconst statusMsg = document.getElementById('status-msg');\n\n// Initialize reels with some symbols\nfunction initReels() {\n    reelStrips.forEach(strip =\u003e {\n        // Create a long strip to simulate infinite spinning\n        for (let i = 0; i \u003c 30; i++) {\n            const symbolDiv = document.createElement('div');\n            symbolDiv.classList.add('symbol');\n            symbolDiv.textContent = symbols[Math.floor(Math.random() * symbols.length)];\n            strip.appendChild(symbolDiv);\n        }\n    });\n}\n\nasync function spin() {\n    if (tokens \u003c SPIN_COST) {\n        statusMsg.textContent = \"GPU POOR! Need more tokens.\";\n        return;\n    }\n\n    tokens -= SPIN_COST;\n    updateUI();\n    spinBtn.disabled = true;\n    statusMsg.textContent = \"Inference in progress...\";\n\n    const results = [];\n\n    // Spin each reel\n    const spinPromises = Array.from(reelStrips).map((strip, index) =\u003e {\n        return new Promise(resolve =\u003e {\n            const randomOffset = Math.floor(Math.random() * (symbols.length * 3));\n            const targetY = randomOffset * 80;\n            \n            // Apply animation\n            strip.style.transition = `transform ${2 + index * 0.5}s cubic-bezier(0.1, 0, 0.1, 1)`;\n            strip.style.transform = `translateY(-${targetY}px)`;\n\n            setTimeout(() =\u003e {\n                // Determine which symbol landed\n                const symbolIndex = (randomOffset) % symbols.length;\n                const actualSymbol = strip.children[randomOffset].textContent;\n                results.push(actualSymbol);\n                resolve();\n            }, 2000 + index * 500);\n        });\n    });\n\n    await Promise.all(spinPromises);\n    checkWin(results);\n    spinBtn.disabled = false;\n}\n\nfunction checkWin(results) {\n    const [s1, s2, s3] = results;\n\n    if (s1 === s2 \u0026\u0026 s2 === s3) {\n        if (s1 === '🤖') {\n            tokens += 100;\n            statusMsg.textContent = \"JACKPOT: AGI ACHIEVED! +100 Tokens\";\n        } else if (s1 === '📉') {\n            tokens -= 50;\n            statusMsg.textContent = \"MODEL COLLAPSE! -50 Tokens\";\n        } else {\n            tokens += 50;\n            statusMsg.textContent = `Synergy detected! +50 Tokens`;\n        }\n    } else {\n        statusMsg.textContent = \"Hallucination detected. Try again.\";\n    }\n    updateUI();\n}\n\nfunction updateUI() {\n    tokenDisplay.textContent = tokens;\n    if (tokens \u003c= 0) {\n        statusMsg.textContent = \"Out of Compute. Please buy the Pro Plan.\";\n        spinBtn.disabled = true;\n    }\n}\n\nspinBtn.addEventListener('click', spin);\ninitReels();\n```\n\n### Engineering Review \u0026 Tips:\n1.  **State Management:** Currently, the tokens are stored in a local variable. For a real app, you'd want to persist this in `localStorage` so the user doesn't lose their \"Compute Credits\" on refresh.\n2.  **CSS Transitions:** Using `transform: translateY` is significantly more performant than animating `top` or `margin-top` because it leverages the GPU and doesn't trigger a reflow of the document.\n3.  **Pseudo-Randomness:** `Math.random()` is fine for a joke app, but for any real gambling software (which I assume you aren't building!), you would need a cryptographically secure source of randomness.\n4.  **UX Trick:** Notice the staggered delay in the reels (`2 + index * 0.5`). This mimics real mechanical slot machines and builds \"suspense\" while the user waits for the result.\n\n\u003c!--\n[PROMPT_SUGGESTION]How can I add sound effects for the spinning and winning states using the Web Audio API?[/PROMPT_SUGGESTION]\n[PROMPT_SUGGESTION]Modify the code to store the token balance in localStorage so it persists after a page refresh.[/PROMPT_SUGGESTION]\n--\u003e","chatSectionId":"2","ideContext":{"currentFile":{"path":"","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0}},"remoteContexts":null,"remoteRepositories":[],"otherFiles":null,"rules":null,"editableRegion":null,"recentUserActions":null,"chatSectionId":"2"},"openFileUri":"output:extension-output-google.geminicodeassist-%232-Gemini%20Code%20Assist","ragStatus":"RAG_DISABLED","timeToFirstToken":"9128","agentProcessingDetails":{},"workspaceChange":{},"fileUsage":{},"suggestedPrompts":["How can I add sound effects for the spinning and winning states using the Web Audio API?","Modify the code to store the token balance in localStorage so it persists after a page refresh."],"thinkingSummaryMarkdownText":"**Conceptualizing the Build**\n\nI'm currently fleshing out the core mechanics for this AI-themed slot machine app. My focus is on crafting the winning and spending token logic first, ensuring it feels responsive and engaging. I'll then move on to the user interface, aiming for a fun, tongue-in-cheek aesthetic that aligns with the AI theme.\n\n\n**Developing the Core Mechanics**\n\nI'm now prioritizing the JavaScript logic. I've defined the symbol array and started writing the `spin` function, focusing on generating those random reel indices. Next up is implementing the win condition checks, which will drive the player's token balance. I am planning on making the satirical messaging extra spicy.\n\n\n**Analyzing the Design Specs**\n\nI'm now carefully examining the specifications. I'm focusing on the UI elements, and I'm planning on using a retro-future aesthetic, with some terminal-style text. The symbols need to feel right.\n\n\n","agentMetadata":{"coderAgent":{"kind":""},"model":""},"modelDisplayName":"3 Flash Preview","modelID":"chat-gemini-3-0-flash-preview-free-tier"}],"ragStatus":"RAG_DISABLED","threadId":"1bc7d5cc-3760-11f1-96d8-5e55762ade97"}
